Check out our live tasting! Chris & Kim taste this week's specialty can & coffee releases, which will all be released this Thursday, July 15th at 9am online. They also show off on our Pure Pride eco-Shirts available now online and in taprooms! All shirt proceeds go to @bravetrails !

MURKWOOD
Murky IPA with Nelson Sauvin & Pacifica Hops
7% ABV

CATACLYSMIC EVENT
Murky Quintuple IPA with Nelson Sauvin, Riwaka, & Citra Cryo Hops
15% ABV

NIGHT ON GHOST MOUNTAIN BARREL-AGED ETHIOPIA GUJI
*Collaboration with @mostracoffee & @lostcausemeadery

All specialty releases will be available for purchase online starting Thursday, July 15th at 9am.

*IMPORTANT: The sale starts at 9am PST on Thursday, July 15th. We anticipate this to be a high-demand sale with a limited number of cans. We recommend being prepared to initiate your purchase right at 9am PST. As always, we appreciate your interest in our beer, and your support and understanding of our efforts as a small boutique brewery.

Details at link in profile.

node.text:
We are proud to source our organic strawberries locally from @jrorganicsfarm. Located just up the road in North County, J.R. Organics is a fourth generation family farm that is California Certified Organic Farmers (CCOF) certified. All of their produce is grown in the purest way possible...including the 10,000 pounds of strawberries that are being added to our strawberry brews this season!

We believe every beer should tell a story. As we celebrate our fifth year in partnership with J.R. Organics, we took our team to the farm to taste the strawberries, check out the fields where they were grown, and get to know the family that grew them. From our brewers to our beertenders, everyone had the opportunity for a hands-on experience to connect with the ingredients. Because of this experience, we can convey the rich story behind the beer—the organic farm, the multi-generational family, the sweetest San Diego strawberries—and enrich your experience when you taste it in your glass.

Learn more at the Strawberry Fest link in our profile.

#pureproject #strawberryfest #jrorganics #organic #strawberries #sdbeer

Strawberry season is upon us and we’re excited to release your favorite strawberry beers again this year, brewed with local organic strawberries from J.R. Organics. Today Chris and Cheyna taste and discuss the first in our Strawberry Fest 2021 lineup, Sunset Crush!

SUNSET CRUSH
Cream Ale with Strawberry & Vanilla
5.8% ABV

A summer twist on our house cream ale, Sunset Crush is full of fruity, bright acidity thanks to 1500 pounds of local, organic strawberries from J.R. Organics. The addition of organic Tahitian vanilla bean creates a sweet and creamy backbone to showcase the strawberries—a true reflection of our local terroir. This refreshing ale got its name for a reason—it is the perfect beer to crush while basking in the beauty of a San Diego sunset.

Sunset Crush will be released on draft at all taprooms on Thursday, May 27th. Come for a fresh pour, or take a fill home with you.

Make sure to follow along as we continue the Strawberry Fest 2021 releases!

#pureproject #strawberryfest #jrorganics #organic #strawberries #sdbeer

The ladies of Pure proudly present Pure Passion, a pale ale brewed for International Women's Collaboration Brew Day.

PURE PASSION
*International Women's Collaboration Brew Day
Pale Ale with Strata, Simcoe, & Motueka Hops
5.5% ABV

Donning an unfiltered straw color and lacy white head, this medium-bodied creation is hopped with Strata, Simcoe, and Motueka. The result is a vibrant lime zest on the nose that transforms to grapefruit on the palate. Complementary essences of peach, guava, pineapple and pine convey the pure passion that the ladies put into this one.

Join us at any of our taprooms for a fresh pour, or take a crowler or growler home with you. We look forward to seeing you!

We are excited to reveal a beautiful new murky creation, Zigsa. Zigsa is incredibly well balanced and this initial batch is as rare as its Tibetan snow leopard namesake; be sure to pick up a 4-pack while it's in sight.

A new imperial stout alongside the coffee beans that went into it. Coming August 5th:

SITUATIONAL GRAVITY
Imperial Stout with Coffee & Vanilla
11.5% ABV

Introducing the third in our new series of core stouts, Situational Gravity. We added organic La Cañada coffee from Oaxaca, Mexico (roasted by our friends at Mostra) and organic Tahitian and Mexican vanilla beans to this imperial stout, resulting in a multi-faceted sensory experience. Aromas of vanilla bean ice cream, dark chocolate, coffee, and blueberry wine give way to flavors of rich chocolate ganache, espresso and caramel amidst a full body and velvety mouthfeel.

SITUATIONAL GRAVITY
Organic Mexico Oaxaca La Cañada Coffee

These organic coffee beans come to us from the Cañada region of Oaxaca, Mexico, where the humidity and altitude create ideal conditions for growing coffee. The beans were grown, washed and sun-dried by our southern neighbors before making their way to San Diego where our friends at Mostra Coffee roasted them for our Situational Gravity imperial stout. Expect a full-bodied dark roast with notes of dulce de leche, chardonnay, and cocoa powder.

Details at link in profile.

Our GABF medal winning Flanders-style red ale returns. Coming August 5th:

ROES RED
Oak Barrel-Aged Flanders Style Red Ale
7% ABV

Presenting batch #6 of our Flanders-style red ale, Roes Red—named after the Belgian town of Roeselare where the style originally developed. This is the first batch aged in our new 1,000-gallon Barolo cask from Italy; the aging process was initiated last year with a 50/50 blend of fresh Roes Red and one-year-old Roes Red, which had previously aged in French oak. The result is a deep red, mahogany-colored ale with notes of oak, cherry, dates, red currants and toast. The complexity of this beer is further driven by Winslow's proprietary blend of yeast strains—Belgian in origin—which produce sour lactic and acetic characteristics. A fresh take on a classic style, Roes Red is beautifully intricate and delightfully refreshing.

Details at link in profile.
